# Page layout

See also: **`page-composition.mdc`**, **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`error-handling.mdc`**, **`accessibility.mdc`**. Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

**File splitting** → `page-composition.mdc`. Cross-feature imports → **`frontend-feature-boundaries.mdc`** (auto-loads on `src/api/**`, `src/lib/**`). This rule owns **spacing rhythm, column alignment, responsive reflow, and visual hierarchy**.

Golden reference: `src/components/layout/`, `src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx`.

Ship for **320px–375px** first. Horizontal overflow on phones is a release blocker.

## When to use `AppPageShell`

| Page type | Layout approach |
| --------- | --------------- |
| **App / dashboard / settings** | `AppPageShell` + `PageHeader` — consistent padding and zone rhythm |
| **Marketing / landing** | Often **full-bleed** sections — `width="full"` or custom layout **without** global `max-w-3xl` |
| **Auth card** | `width="narrow"` or centered card outside the shell |

**Pick width per route** — do not force every page through `max-w-3xl`. Adjust presets in `layout.constants.ts`.

## Layout primitives

| Component | Purpose |
| --------- | ------- |
| **`AppPageShell`** | Shared page padding, vertical zone rhythm (`gap-8`), optional max-width |
| **`PageHeader`** | Title + description (`gap-1`) + optional action slot |
| **`PageSection`** | Major page zones; optional `border-t pt-8` for phase changes |

```tsx
<AppPageShell width="default">
  <PageHeader title="Items" description="Manage your workspace." action={<Actions />} />
  <PageSection>{/* status / alerts */}</PageSection>
  <PageSection bordered>{/* primary workspace */}</PageSection>
</AppPageShell>
```

When a route needs full width:

```tsx
<AppPageShell width="full">
  <section className="…">{/* hero */}</section>
  <section className="mx-auto max-w-5xl …">{/* optional inner cap */}</section>
</AppPageShell>
```

**Do not** hand-roll `py-8` + `max-w-*` on every app page.

### Width presets (`AppPageShell`)

| `width` | Default class | Typical intent |
| ------- | ------------- | -------------- |
| `default` | `max-w-3xl` | Standard app content column |
| `profile` | `max-w-2xl` | Focused forms, account settings |
| `narrow` | `max-w-lg` | Auth, compact panels |
| `full` | `max-w-none` | Landing pages, wide layouts |

When app chrome and page body share a column, use the **same** `appContentWidthClass` + `appContentPaddingClass` from `@/components/layout`.

## Spacing rhythm

| Level | Gap | Use |
| ----- | --- | --- |
| Page zones | `gap-8` | Between header, alerts, main workspace |
| Section interior | `gap-4`–`gap-6` | Tabs → toolbar → card |
| Status / alerts stack | `gap-3` | Multiple alerts |
| Title block | `gap-1` | `PageHeader` title + description |
| Dense lists | `gap-2` | Rows, metadata lines |

## Shell alignment

- **`RootLayout` `<main>`** — `pb-10`; skip link + `#main` (`accessibility.mdc`).
- **Chrome vs body** — same max-width when both constrained.
- **Padding** — `px-4 sm:px-6`, `py-8 sm:py-10` via `AppPageShell`.

## Visual hierarchy

| Element | Weight |
| ------- | ------ |
| Page title | `PageHeader` `h1` |
| Status / alerts | `Alert` above workspace, `gap-3` stack |
| Primary workspace | `border-t pt-8` separation |
| Secondary lists | Flat rows — `gap-2`; avoid nested `CardContent` for one metadata line |

- **Long copy** — `text-pretty` on descriptions.
- **Tinted panels** — semantic tokens, not `text-muted-foreground` on strong washes (`design-tokens.mdc`).

## Responsive & mobile

Every layout must **reflow without horizontal scroll** at narrow widths.

### App shell navigation

**Do not** put unbounded horizontal link rows in the header.

| Viewport | Pattern |
| -------- | ------- |
| `< md` | `Sheet` / hamburger, bottom tabs, or scrollable tabs — pick one per app |
| `≥ md` | Full horizontal nav OK |

Test at **320px and 375px** before merge.

### Touch targets (WCAG 2.5.5)

Minimum **44×44 CSS px** hit area on touch devices.

| Control | Pattern |
| ------- | ------- |
| Primary actions | shadcn `Button` (`size="default"` / `size="icon"`) |
| Pager dots, tiny icons | `min-h-11 min-w-11` wrapper — not `size-2` alone |
| List icon actions | `Button variant="ghost" size="icon"` — not `h-7 w-7` raw `<button>` |

### Primary CTAs on mobile

Main actions (Save, Generate, Submit): **`w-full sm:w-auto`**. Use `PageFooterActions` or `border-t pt-6` + stacked buttons below `sm`.

### Layout patterns

- **`flex` + `gap-*`** and **`min-w-0`** on flex children that truncate.
- Tables on mobile → card list, horizontal scroll with affordance, or column hiding.
- Grids: `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` — not fixed `grid-cols-4` on all viewports.
- Breakpoints: Tailwind `sm`, `md`, `lg`; `hidden md:flex` — not JS width checks unless necessary.

## Loading & empty

- Skeleton **mirrors final structure** — not one gray block (`error-handling.mdc`).
- Empty states **teach** — dashed border + hint; not bare alert text.

## Interaction on actions

- Async buttons: `aria-busy`, disabled while pending, label changes (`Saving…`, `Loading…`).
- Disable when preconditions fail.

## Checklist

- [ ] App routes use `AppPageShell` + `PageHeader` or documented full-bleed layout.
- [ ] Width preset matches route intent; landing pages not forced into `max-w-3xl`.
- [ ] Chrome and body columns align when both constrained.
- [ ] Major phases separated (`gap-8`, `border-t pt-8`).
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at 320px on changed routes.
- [ ] App nav collapses or adapts below `md`.
- [ ] Primary mobile CTAs full-width; custom icon buttons meet 44×44 (or shadcn `Button size="icon"`).
- [ ] Lists stay flat; skeletons and empty states match structure.
